<h2 id="monte-carlo-markov-chain">Monte Carlo Markov Chain</h2>

<p>Markov Chain:</p>

<p>Ergodocity:</p>

<p>Run it long enough, you’ll eventually get a point that comes from P ?</p>

<p>Theorem:
if X_0, X_1, .. in an irreducible, time-homogeneous, discret Markov Chain with a stationary distribution pi, then:</p>

<p>In other words, we could use the state that the Markov Chain converges as a sample of pi! Let it sink in.</p>

